      "solution": "height = int(input())\nwidth = int(input())\nshifts = int(input())\ncharacter = input()\noldX = 0\noldY = 0\nfor y in range(height):\n    row = input()\n    x = row.find(character)\n    if x != -1:\n        oldX = x\n        oldY = y\n        break \n\nwhile shifts > 0:\n    if oldX + 1 > width-1:\n        if oldY + 1 > height-1:\n            oldY = 0\n            oldX = 0\n        else:\n            oldX = 0\n            oldY += 1\n    else:\n        oldX += 1\n    shifts-=1\n\nfor i in range(height):\n    for j in range(width):\n        if i == oldY and j == oldX:\n            print(character, end = '')\n        else:\n            print('_',end = '')\n    print()\n    \n",
